    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Wheeling</placeName>
                <date>March 21. 1854</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have recd. your letter<lb/> of bill for the Occident.
                    <sic>Inclosed</sic> you will find<lb/> Six dolls.$6. <persName>Mr
                    Bloch</persName> &amp; <persName>Mr Heyman</persName>, have requested<lb/> me,
                to inform you, that they will soon be<lb/> in <placeName>Philaa.</placeName> as they
                prefer to see the bible<lb/> before selecting one. I will send my order with<lb/>
                one of these gentlemen, or probably call on you<lb/> personally. I have added one
                subscriber<lb/> for the Occident, address. <persName>Mr. M. Moss</persName>.<lb/> of
                this place, send him the <date>March</date> number.<lb/> I will cheerfully continue
                my exertions, to get subscribers, for your invaluable publication,<lb/> we have an
                    <sic>organised</sic> congregation here,<lb/> numbering from 25 to 30 members,
                &amp; have also a<lb/> Synagogue there are residing here 17 Jewish<lb/> families,
                The names of the officers of the Congregation,<lb/> are. <persName>Julius
                    Ballenburg</persName> President, <persName>Mr. M. Moss</persName><lb/>
                Secretary, Treasurer <persName>Adolph Ballenburg</persName>, the<lb/> congregation
                have just elected <persName>Mr Joel<lb/> Eppinger</persName>, of
                    <placeName>Bechhofen, Bavaria</placeName>, &amp; lately of<lb/>
                <placeName>Cincinnati, Ohio</placeName>, to act as Shochet, Hazan,<lb/> &amp;
                Teacher.</p>
            <p>Very Respectfully your friend &amp; subscriber.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Daniel Stein</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
